\title{Clinvar Database}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Query NCBI ClinVar for variant clinical significance. Search by gene/position, interpret pathogenicity classifications, access via E-utilities API or FTP, annotate VCFs, for genomic medicine."}

\subtree{
\title{ClinVar Database}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{ClinVar is NCBI's freely accessible archive of reports on relationships between human genetic variants and phenotypes, with supporting evidence. The database aggregates information about genomic variation and its relationship to human health, providing standardized variant classifications used in clinical genetics and research.}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\p{This skill should be used when:}

\ul{
\li{Searching for variants by gene, condition, or clinical significance}
\li{Interpreting clinical significance classifications (pathogenic, benign, VUS)}
\li{Accessing ClinVar data programmatically via E-utilities API}
\li{Downloading and processing bulk data from FTP}
\li{Understanding review status and star ratings}
\li{Resolving conflicting variant interpretations}
\li{Annotating variant call sets with clinical significance}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Capabilities}
\subtree{
\title{1. Search and Query ClinVar}
\subtree{
\title{Web Interface Queries}
\p{Search ClinVar using the web interface at https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/clinvar/}

\p{\strong{Common search patterns:}}

\ul{
\li{By gene: \code{\startverb BRCA1[gene]\stopverb}}
\li{By clinical significance: \code{\startverb pathogenic[CLNSIG]\stopverb}}
\li{By condition: \code{\startverb breast cancer[disorder]\stopverb}}
\li{By variant: \code{\startverb NM_000059.3:c.1310_1313del[variant name]\stopverb}}
\li{By chromosome: \code{\startverb 13[chr]\stopverb}}
\li{Combined: \code{\startverb BRCA1[gene] AND pathogenic[CLNSIG]\stopverb}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Programmatic Access via E-utilities}
\p{Access ClinVar programmatically using NCBI's E-utilities API. Refer to \code{\startverb references/api_reference.md\stopverb} for comprehensive API documentation including:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{esearch} - Search for variants matching criteria}
\li{\strong{esummary} - Retrieve variant summaries}
\li{\strong{efetch} - Download full XML records}
\li{\strong{elink} - Find related records in other NCBI databases}
}

\p{\strong{Quick example using curl:}}

\pre{\startverb
# Search for pathogenic BRCA1 variants
curl "https://eutils.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/esearch.fcgi?db=clinvar&term=BRCA1[gene]+AND+pathogenic[CLNSIG]&retmode=json"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Best practices:}}

\ul{
\li{Test queries on the web interface before automating}
\li{Use API keys to increase rate limits from 3 to 10 requests/second}
\li{Implement exponential backoff for rate limit errors}
\li{Set \code{\startverb Entrez.email\stopverb} when using Biopython}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Interpret Clinical Significance}
\subtree{
\title{Understanding Classifications}
\p{ClinVar uses standardized terminology for variant classifications. Refer to \code{\startverb references/clinical_significance.md\stopverb} for detailed interpretation guidelines.}

\p{\strong{Key germline classification terms (ACMG/AMP):}}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Pathogenic (P)} - Variant causes disease (~99\% probability)}
\li{\strong{Likely Pathogenic (LP)} - Variant likely causes disease (~90\% probability)}
\li{\strong{Uncertain Significance (VUS)} - Insufficient evidence to classify}
\li{\strong{Likely Benign (LB)} - Variant likely does not cause disease}
\li{\strong{Benign (B)} - Variant does not cause disease}
}

\p{\strong{Review status (star ratings):}}

\ul{
\li{★★★★ Practice guideline - Highest confidence}
\li{★★★ Expert panel review (e.g., ClinGen) - High confidence}
\li{★★ Multiple submitters, no conflicts - Moderate confidence}
\li{★ Single submitter with criteria - Standard weight}
\li{☆ No assertion criteria - Low confidence}
}

\p{\strong{Critical considerations:}}

\ul{
\li{Always check review status - prefer ★★★ or ★★★★ ratings}
\li{Conflicting interpretations require manual evaluation}
\li{Classifications may change as new evidence emerges}
\li{VUS (uncertain significance) variants lack sufficient evidence for clinical use}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Download Bulk Data from FTP}
\subtree{
\title{Access ClinVar FTP Site}
\p{Download complete datasets from \code{\startverb ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pub/clinvar/\stopverb}}

\p{Refer to \code{\startverb references/data_formats.md\stopverb} for comprehensive documentation on file formats and processing.}

\p{\strong{Update schedule:}}

\ul{
\li{Monthly releases: First Thursday of each month (complete dataset, archived)}
\li{Weekly updates: Every Monday (incremental updates)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Available Formats}
\p{\strong{XML files} (most comprehensive):}

\ul{
\li{VCV (Variation) files: \code{\startverb xml/clinvar_variation/\stopverb} - Variant-centric aggregation}
\li{RCV (Record) files: \code{\startverb xml/RCV/\stopverb} - Variant-condition pairs}
\li{Include full submission details, evidence, and metadata}
}

\p{\strong{VCF files} (for genomic pipelines):}

\ul{
\li{GRCh37: \code{\startverb vcf_GRCh37/clinvar.vcf.gz\stopverb}}
\li{GRCh38: \code{\startverb vcf_GRCh38/clinvar.vcf.gz\stopverb}}
\li{Limitations: Excludes variants >10kb and complex structural variants}
}

\p{\strong{Tab-delimited files} (for quick analysis):}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb tab_delimited/variant_summary.txt.gz\stopverb} - Summary of all variants}
\li{\code{\startverb tab_delimited/var_citations.txt.gz\stopverb} - PubMed citations}
\li{\code{\startverb tab_delimited/cross_references.txt.gz\stopverb} - Database cross-references}
}

\p{\strong{Example download:}}

\pre{\startverb
# Download latest monthly XML release
wget ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pub/clinvar/xml/clinvar_variation/ClinVarVariationRelease_00-latest.xml.gz

# Download VCF for GRCh38
wget ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pub/clinvar/vcf_GRCh38/clinvar.vcf.gz
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Process and Analyze ClinVar Data}
\subtree{
\title{Working with XML Files}
\p{Process XML files to extract variant details, classifications, and evidence.}

\p{\strong{Python example with xml.etree:}}

\pre{\startverb
import gzip
import xml.etree.ElementTree as ET

with gzip.open('ClinVarVariationRelease.xml.gz', 'rt') as f:
    for event, elem in ET.iterparse(f, events=('end',)):
        if elem.tag == 'VariationArchive':
            variation_id = elem.attrib.get('VariationID')
            # Extract clinical significance, review status, etc.
            elem.clear()  # Free memory
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Working with VCF Files}
\p{Annotate variant calls or filter by clinical significance using bcftools or Python.}

\p{\strong{Using bcftools:}}

\pre{\startverb
# Filter pathogenic variants
bcftools view -i 'INFO/CLNSIG~"Pathogenic"' clinvar.vcf.gz

# Extract specific genes
bcftools view -i 'INFO/GENEINFO~"BRCA"' clinvar.vcf.gz

# Annotate your VCF with ClinVar
bcftools annotate -a clinvar.vcf.gz -c INFO your_variants.vcf
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Using PyVCF in Python:}}

\pre{\startverb
import vcf

vcf_reader = vcf.Reader(filename='clinvar.vcf.gz')
for record in vcf_reader:
    clnsig = record.INFO.get('CLNSIG', [])
    if 'Pathogenic' in clnsig:
        gene = record.INFO.get('GENEINFO', [''])[0]
        print(f"{record.CHROM}:{record.POS} {gene} - {clnsig}")
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Working with Tab-Delimited Files}
\p{Use pandas or command-line tools for rapid filtering and analysis.}

\p{\strong{Using pandas:}}

\pre{\startverb
import pandas as pd

# Load variant summary
df = pd.read_csv('variant_summary.txt.gz', sep='\t', compression='gzip')

# Filter pathogenic variants in specific gene
pathogenic_brca = df[
    (df['GeneSymbol'] == 'BRCA1') &
    (df['ClinicalSignificance'].str.contains('Pathogenic', na=False))
]

# Count variants by clinical significance
sig_counts = df['ClinicalSignificance'].value_counts()
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Using command-line tools:}}

\pre{\startverb
# Extract pathogenic variants for specific gene
zcat variant_summary.txt.gz | \
  awk -F'\t' '$7=="TP53" && $13~"Pathogenic"' | \
  cut -f1,5,7,13,14
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{5. Handle Conflicting Interpretations}
\p{When multiple submitters provide different classifications for the same variant, ClinVar reports "Conflicting interpretations of pathogenicity."}

\p{\strong{Resolution strategy:}}

\ol{
\li{Check review status (star rating) - higher ratings carry more weight}
\li{Examine evidence and assertion criteria from each submitter}
\li{Consider submission dates - newer submissions may reflect updated evidence}
\li{Review population frequency data (e.g., gnomAD) for context}
\li{Consult expert panel classifications (★★★) when available}
\li{For clinical use, always defer to a genetics professional}
}

\p{\strong{Search query to exclude conflicts:}}

\pre{\startverb
TP53[gene] AND pathogenic[CLNSIG] NOT conflicting[RVSTAT]
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{6. Track Classification Updates}
\p{Variant classifications may change over time as new evidence emerges.}

\p{\strong{Why classifications change:}}

\ul{
\li{New functional studies or clinical data}
\li{Updated population frequency information}
\li{Revised ACMG/AMP guidelines}
\li{Segregation data from additional families}
}

\p{\strong{Best practices:}}

\ul{
\li{Document ClinVar version and access date for reproducibility}
\li{Re-check classifications periodically for critical variants}
\li{Subscribe to ClinVar mailing list for major updates}
\li{Use monthly archived releases for stable datasets}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{7. Submit Data to ClinVar}
\p{Organizations can submit variant interpretations to ClinVar.}

\p{\strong{Submission methods:}}

\ul{
\li{Web submission portal: https://submit.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/subs/clinvar/}
\li{API submission (requires service account): See \code{\startverb references/api_reference.md\stopverb}}
\li{Batch submission via Excel templates}
}

\p{\strong{Requirements:}}

\ul{
\li{Organizational account with NCBI}
\li{Assertion criteria (preferably ACMG/AMP guidelines)}
\li{Supporting evidence for classification}
}

\p{Contact: clinvar@ncbi.nlm.nih.gov for submission account setup.}
}
}

